verbose_text: Kao et al XREF_BIBR found a small molecular, nucleozin (NCZ, Figure XREF_FIG), which may inhibit the infection caused by the H1N1, H3N2 and H5N1 strains as it can initiate the aggregation process of NP, blocking its nuclear accumulation (with EC 50 s of 0.069 muM, 0.16 muM and 0.33 muM showd in MDCK cell based Plaque Reduction Assay, respectively).
evidence: caused by the H1N1, H3N2 and H5N1 strains as it can initiate the aggregation process of NP
